<paragraph id="8BB336FB3237FFDD83E9FAD02DB8FAF6" blockId="8.[151,1437,1303,2013]" box="[151,403,1303,1329]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading id="D0FB81973237FFDD83E9FAD02DB8FAF6" box="[151,403,1303,1329]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="5">
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D783237FFDD83E9FAD02DB8FAF6" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[151,403,1303,1329]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cerradomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subflavus">
<emphasis id="B978EAE93237FFDD83E9FAD02DB8FAF6" box="[151,403,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cerradomys subflavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB336FB3237FFDD83B9FAFC2876F8EE" blockId="8.[151,1437,1303,2013]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Karyotype: 2n = 54 and FN = 62. Autosomal complement: three large submetacentric pairs, two small metacentric pairs, and 21 acrocentric pairs medium to small decreasing in size. Sex chromosomes: X chromosome presented two different morphologies, a large acrocentric (Xa), and a large subtelocentric (Xb); Y chromosome presented two different morphologies, a medium acrocentric (Ya), and a large acrocentric (Yb) (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3237FFDD8714FA602D20FA22" author="Almeida, E. J. C. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y." pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="129 - 137" refId="ref63448" refString="Almeida, E. J. C. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. (1985) Robertsonian fusion, pericentric inversion and sex chromosome heteromorphisms in Oryzomys subflavus (Cricetidae, Rodentia). Caryologia, 38 (2), 129 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00087114.1985.10797737" type="journal article" year="1985">Almeida &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda 1985</bibRefCitation>
, pp. 132, 
<figureCitation id="13372A7E3237FFDD8201FA0C2DEFFA22" box="[383,452,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1191,1215]" captionTargetBox="[159,1426,281,1162]" captionTargetId="figure-69@7.[151,1436,273,1168]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens of genus Cerradomys. (□) C. akroai; (■) C. goytaca; (ê) C. langguthi; (r) C. maracajuensis; (▲) C. marinhus; (○) C. scotti; (☆) C. subflavus; (l) C. vivoi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423619/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3237FFDD82ACFA0C2F36FA22" author="Langguth, A. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R." box="[466,797,1483,1509]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="285 - 294" refId="ref68527" refString="Langguth, A. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R. (2002) The Oryzomys subflavus species group, with description of two new species (Rodentia, Muridae, Sigmodontinae). Arquivos do Museu Nacional, 60 (4), 285 - 294." type="journal article" year="2002">Langguth &amp; Bonvicino 2002</bibRefCitation>
). Two different morphologies of sex chromosomes were recognized by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3237FFDD8242FA282E64F9CE" author="Percequillo, A. R. &amp; Hingst-Zaher, E. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R." box="[316,591,1519,1545]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 46" refId="ref71570" refString="Percequillo, A. R., Hingst-Zaher, E. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R. (2008) Systematic review of genus Cerradomys Weksler, Percequillo and Voss, 2006 (Rodentia: Cricetidae: Sigmodontinae: Oryzomyini), with description of two new species from eastern Brazil. American Museum Novitates, 3622, 1 - 46. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 495.1" type="journal article" year="2008">
Percequillo 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93237FFDD82BDFA282DDFF9CE" box="[451,500,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
. (2008)
</bibRefCitation>
, a medium acrocentric X and a small acrocentric Y. Variation in diploid (2n = 55 and 2n = 56) and fundamental number (FN = 63) were reported resulting from centric fusions affecting one large submetacentric pair (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3237FFDD82BCF9F02E9DF996" author="Yonenaga, Y. &amp; Frota-Pessoa, O. &amp; Kasahara, S. &amp; Almeida, E. J. C." box="[450,694,1591,1617]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="202 - 211" refId="ref76160" refString="Yonenaga, Y., Frota-Pessoa, O., Kasahara, S. &amp; Almeida, E. J. C. (1976) Cytogenetic studies on Brazilian rodents. Ciencia e cultura, 28 (2), 202 - 211." type="journal article" year="1976">
Yonenaga 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93237FFDD8145F9F02E46F996" box="[571,621,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
. 1976
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3237FFDD81BFF9F02875F996" author="Almeida, E. J. C. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y." box="[705,1118,1590,1617]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="129 - 137" refId="ref63448" refString="Almeida, E. J. C. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. (1985) Robertsonian fusion, pericentric inversion and sex chromosome heteromorphisms in Oryzomys subflavus (Cricetidae, Rodentia). Caryologia, 38 (2), 129 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00087114.1985.10797737" type="journal article" year="1985">Almeida &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda 1985</bibRefCitation>
). C-banding metaphases exhibited blocks of constitutive heterochromatin on the pericentromeric region of all autosomes, with the exception of the three submetacentric pairs, in this case only a discrete staining was observed. The Xb exhibited constitutive heterochromatin on the short arm, on the centromeric and proximal region of long arm, and an interstitial C-band was observed on its long arm. The Ya presented a large heterochromatic block on the distal portion of its long arm, amounting to about two-thirds of its length, while no heterochromatin material was detected on the pericentromeric region. G- and Q-banding were also performed (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3237FFDD81CAF8C8287BF8EE" author="Almeida, E. J. C. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y." box="[692,1104,1806,1833]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="129 - 137" refId="ref63448" refString="Almeida, E. J. C. &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda, Y. (1985) Robertsonian fusion, pericentric inversion and sex chromosome heteromorphisms in Oryzomys subflavus (Cricetidae, Rodentia). Caryologia, 38 (2), 129 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00087114.1985.10797737" type="journal article" year="1985">Almeida &amp; Yonenaga-Yassuda 1985</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31665703237FFDD83B9F8F428F8F81A" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB336FB3237FFDD83B9F8F428F8F81A" blockId="8.[151,1437,1303,2013]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Another karyotype with 2n = 54 and FN = 64 was reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3237FFDD80FFF8F4285DF88A" author="Paresque, R. &amp; Souza, W. P. &amp; Mendes, S. L. &amp; Fagundes, V." box="[897,1142,1843,1869]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="5 - 33" refId="ref70883" refString="Paresque, R., Souza, W. P., Mendes, S. L. &amp; Fagundes, V. (2004) Composicao cariotipica da fauna de roedores e marsupiais de duas areas de Mata Atlantica do Espirito Santo, Brasil. Boletim do Museu de Biologia Mello Leitao, 17, 5 - 33." type="journal article" year="2004">
Paresque 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93237FFDD8092F8F42836F88A" box="[1004,1053,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
. (2004)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3237FFDD87D5F8F429B3F88A" author="Moreira, J. C. &amp; Manduca, E. G. &amp; Goncalves, P. R. &amp; Morais Jr, M. D. &amp; Pereira, R. F. &amp; Lessa, G. &amp; Dergam, J. A." box="[1195,1432,1843,1869]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="103 - 118" refId="ref69612" refString="Moreira, J. C., Manduca, E. G., Goncalves, P. R., Morais Jr, M. D., Pereira, R. F., Lessa, G. &amp; Dergam, J. A. (2009) Small mammals from Serra do Brigadeiro State Park, Minas Gerais, southeastern Brazil: species composition and elevational distribution. Arquivos do Museu Nacional, 67, 103 - 118." type="journal article" year="2009">
Moreira 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93237FFDD8672F8F42916F88A" box="[1292,1341,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
. (2009)
</bibRefCitation>
. The difference in the fundamental number was due to the presence of one small metacentric pair instead of an acrocentric one. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B0A3237FFDD8247F8BC2E02F852" author="Moreira, J. C. &amp; Manduca, E. G. &amp; Goncalves, P. R. &amp; Morais Jr, M. D. &amp; Pereira, R. F. &amp; Lessa, G. &amp; Dergam, J. A." box="[313,553,1915,1941]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="103 - 118" refId="ref69612" refString="Moreira, J. C., Manduca, E. G., Goncalves, P. R., Morais Jr, M. D., Pereira, R. F., Lessa, G. &amp; Dergam, J. A. (2009) Small mammals from Serra do Brigadeiro State Park, Minas Gerais, southeastern Brazil: species composition and elevational distribution. Arquivos do Museu Nacional, 67, 103 - 118." type="journal article" year="2009">
Moreira 
<emphasis id="B978EAE93237FFDD82E5F8BC2DE6F852" box="[411,461,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
. (2009)
</bibRefCitation>
, presented another morphology for the Y chromosome, being a medium metacentric. These variations in diploid and fundamental number of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D783237FFDD8009F858282FF87E" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[887,1028,1951,1977]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cerradomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subflavus">
<emphasis id="B978EAE93237FFDD8009F858282FF87E" box="[887,1028,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">C. subflavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs sympatrically on specimens collected in 
<collectingRegion id="49C8F8193237FFDD825EF8042D4FF81A" box="[288,356,1987,2013]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49C8F8193237FFDD8211F8042E39F81A" box="[367,530,1987,2013]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49C8F8193237FFDD8163F8042E98F81A" box="[541,691,1987,2013]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49C8F8193237FFDD8197F8042F76F81A" box="[745,861,1987,2013]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, states of 
<collectingCountry id="F31B766B3237FFDD80B2F804283BF81A" box="[972,1040,1987,2013]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<tableCitation id="C68E03403237FFDD8760F804285EF81A" box="[1054,1141,1987,2013]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="9.[151,235,587,612]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="TABLE 2. Karyotype data of genus Cerradomys. Species, diploid (2n) and fundamental (FN) numbers, collection localities, geographic coordinates and reference." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Table 2</tableCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13372A7E3237FFDD87FFF80428EEF81A" box="[1153,1221,1987,2013]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1191,1215]" captionTargetBox="[159,1426,281,1162]" captionTargetId="figure-69@7.[151,1436,273,1168]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens of genus Cerradomys. (□) C. akroai; (■) C. goytaca; (ê) C. langguthi; (r) C. maracajuensis; (▲) C. marinhus; (○) C. scotti; (☆) C. subflavus; (l) C. vivoi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423619/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
